<paragraph id="3F38ED55720E069EECE0C280972E3234" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Redescription.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4D54BCF7E70F7DB2D11F94CD955B32C5" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
<emphasis id="B3992C6DC36CDBFDFF94CCE74B94C4E6" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Male. Coloration</emphasis>
: Medium body, yellowish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9F2FCE17CF02D7A10ED097642E29174C" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Episymploce wulingensis (Feng et Woo, 1993) comb. nov., male: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690406" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">6A, B</figureCitation>
). Ocelli pale yellow; base of antenna brown, the rest dark brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F279F022DD40307D84C7A7AC64DEDBB0" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Episymploce wulingensis (Feng et Woo, 1993) comb. nov., male: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690406" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">6C</figureCitation>
). The fourth and fifth maxillary palps dark brown, the rest yellow brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="949BA1F4E92A7F01933FBD3B13A626FE" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Episymploce wulingensis (Feng et Woo, 1993) comb. nov., male: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690406" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">6E</figureCitation>
). Pronotum yellowish with a pair of reddish-brown V-shaped stripes, and lateral border yellowish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6E230548F3B180A385E77875CBA489E0" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Episymploce wulingensis (Feng et Woo, 1993) comb. nov., male: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690406" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">6D</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="CE23BEC1B31BA9E0D6EC9BCF15E567AF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Head</emphasis>
: Interocular space less than the distance between ocelli and narrower than width of antennal sockets (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="60215DE27191041AE01ADE7B0C6F743B" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Episymploce wulingensis (Feng et Woo, 1993) comb. nov., male: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690406" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">6C</figureCitation>
). First three segments of maxillary palps almost the same length (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B0A9E092701723CD07F745CC21A12B04" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Episymploce wulingensis (Feng et Woo, 1993) comb. nov., male: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690406" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">6E</figureCitation>
). Pronotum subelliptical, hind margin slightly convex in the middle (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7B6D0AADC27651E81B5D92F7890104CA" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Episymploce wulingensis (Feng et Woo, 1993) comb. nov., male: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690406" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">6D</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="A3382649DFE6D93B3D7FB3002FE32A92" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Tegmina and hindwings</emphasis>
: Both fully developed, extending beyond the end of abdomen (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C129E5A81385C74F796C46D8D79B6788" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Episymploce wulingensis (Feng et Woo, 1993) comb. nov., male: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690406" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">6H, I</figureCitation>
). RP of hindwings with branches near the middle; M simple and unbranched; CuA with 3 complete branches and many small incomplete branches, apical triangle small but visible (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="ADEE8C038ED85618895D4A13AE1B255B" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Episymploce wulingensis (Feng et Woo, 1993) comb. nov., male: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690406" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">6I</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="44FA36A51FF3A250D98796B7B52E50F6" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Legs</emphasis>
: Front femur Type A3 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E6FA1C077401487B252984FF63B31FB9" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Episymploce wulingensis (Feng et Woo, 1993) comb. nov., male: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690406" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">6F</figureCitation>
), pretarsal claws symmetrical and unspecialized, pulvillus present. 
<emphasis id="EDECDADC5E3B00CD4E052E1B2F8ACF92" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Abdominal tergites</emphasis>
: T1 unspecialized, T7 specialized with a pair of shallow fossae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5AB07F41D2A65881379BE9501A12A6A0" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Episymploce wulingensis (Feng et Woo, 1993) comb. nov., male: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690406" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">6G</figureCitation>
), lateral plates of T9 similar. T10 symmetrical and trapezoidal. 
<emphasis id="80EEB8842303355780BB72F3EC75A931" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Paraprocts</emphasis>
: Dissimilar, base of right one with a curved and long spine-like process; left one with a curved finger-like process on which three small thorns are situated (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5BABD63693E1E646EF43CD278C10B751" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Episymploce wulingensis (Feng et Woo, 1993) comb. nov., male: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690406" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">6J</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="81E3876E8EBA229A433B525EB2C0053E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Subgenital plate</emphasis>
: Asymmetrical, both margins curly and covered with thin thorns. Left stylus bifurcated and obtuse angle present; right stylus near the left one, with 2 or 3 branches near the apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="680A03858D797F07EF86A1FE61E32C68" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Episymploce wulingensis (Feng et Woo, 1993) comb. nov., male: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690406" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">6N</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B84537A35AEA8E71E7E507B19A4C64E0" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: L3 on left side, and apex with a deep incision (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="10BCD0E76AE61A654D03BE373E82D153" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Episymploce wulingensis (Feng et Woo, 1993) comb. nov., male: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690406" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">6K</figureCitation>
); L2vm rod-shaped and apex branched (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="645D7F09DC399D9740CAF6C9880329FD" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Episymploce wulingensis (Feng et Woo, 1993) comb. nov., male: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690406" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">6L</figureCitation>
); R2, R3 consisting of several irregular sclerites (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8FE397B52D9670CC9639DE6723717D28" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Episymploce wulingensis (Feng et Woo, 1993) comb. nov., male: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690406" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">6M</figureCitation>
). - 
<emphasis id="720E570BCE23E90A6168F295DAC52E27" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
