<subSubSection id="12DE6F9F6B113A6816CE34BB9A10DDCC" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="6C18B6CC7B35D55FF15F1F80EDEB1B3E" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="235F1D4003640C0AD1B6DC0E8BA09BF3" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
<bibRefCitation id="932D27A741DF044AF6FCB504A561EB09" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.337.5770" author="Wang, ZQ" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" pagination="1 - 18" refId="B55" refString="Wang, ZQ, Che, YL, 2013. Three new species of cockroach genus Symploce Hebard, 1916 (Blattodea, Ectobiidae, Blattellinae) with redescriptions of two known species based on types from Mainland China. ZooKeys 337: 1 - 18, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.337.5770" title="Three new species of cockroach genus Symploce Hebard, 1916 (Blattodea, Ectobiidae, Blattellinae) with redescriptions of two known species based on types from Mainland China." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.337.5770" volume="337" year="2013">Wang and Che (2013)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that 
<taxonomicName id="169AF9EF9856884A51330C4BB3A64B4A" authorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce wulingensis" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wulingensis">
<emphasis id="59C31B2BED7E78C2753FC8DED8FDD576" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce wulingensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Feng and Woo, 1993 should be transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="2BF1E03D58D41249CB0B528B8DAF567E" authorityName="Bey-Bienko" authorityYear="1950" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Episymploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Episymploce" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="065D61C88C92D917175C6A85FD475692" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Episymploce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to the morphological characters. In this paper, we also consider it more appropriate to move this species to 
<taxonomicName id="87BA7986F9774AD4BFC798E858EA7B09" authorityName="Bey-Bienko" authorityYear="1950" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Episymploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Episymploce" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="86A29A34038F6A66D744F168D2291EDF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Episymploce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on basis of the morphological information: body size medium, T7 specialized with a pair of shallow fossae without setae, subgenital plates lightly incrassate and setaceous. Our phylogenetic analysis also supports this view (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="23449E93BBCA914CCA1FDA9512D3C158" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Maximum likelihood (ML) tree based on three mitochondrial genes 12 S rRNA, 16 S rRNA, COII and two nuclear genes 28 S rRNA, histone H 3. The topologies yielded by Bayesian inference (BI) are almost identical with ML tree (see supplementary material Fig. S 1). Branch labels provide bootstrap support (bs) of nodes in ML and posterior probability (pp) (%) of nodes in BI; (*) indicates the branch label of the corresponding analysis is 100 or 1.0, respectively; (-) means the node is absent for the given analysis." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690401" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">1</figureCitation>
, supplementary material Fig. S1): 
<taxonomicName id="E476AF99380511197070C3C0980E9B76" authorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce wulingensis" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wulingensis">
<emphasis id="91BE43FBD21CC25E9658941B68634AF8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce wulingensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Feng and Woo was placed as the sister of 
<taxonomicName id="17BC9AC8854DE7815D27F2D9462BBE05" authorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Feng and Woo" baseAuthorityYear="1999" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Episymploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Episymploce torchaceus" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torchaceus">
<emphasis id="95CAEDDBF52CDD729F28950EC3156DF4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Episymploce torchaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which together were deeply embedded within the clade of 
<taxonomicName id="73366EE14B22AFE0333D9EA8303A1E55" authorityName="Bey-Bienko" authorityYear="1950" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Episymploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Episymploce" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CCCBE56FC0C8DC50D9B5513EEB7E8B2D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Episymploce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B483DA2F5FFF650C604937B08886528B" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="1511D6953DEAAF165DFF3DE7D8036EC0" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8612F128A0A52905361A39DB23DD4E5F" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">China (Fujian, Guangdong, Hainan, Guangxi, Sichuan, Guizhou, Chongqing).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
